🌟 Exciting News: I am so honored to serve on the Advisory Board for the Veritas School of Social Sciences! @VeritasGeorgia 🌟

I am thrilled to announce my new role on the Advisory Board of the nationally acclaimed Veritas School of Social Sciences. This is an incredible opportunity to contribute to a cause close to my heart - empowering the next generation of Black and brown youth through education.

Veritas is most known for our award-winning flagship program Veritas Debate Institute, which has trained over 200 Black and brown youth to compete at Harvard's international summer debate competition where they are SIX-TIME CONSECUTIVE CHAMPIONS 🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆 

📚 Why is this important?

🌟 Representation Matters: Our society is diverse, and our educational institutions should be as well. By actively supporting the education of Black and brown youth, we pave the way for more inclusive and equitable learning environments where all students can thrive.

🌟 Breaking Down Barriers: Quality education is a powerful tool for breaking down systemic barriers. By investing in educational opportunities for Black and brown students, we not only give them a chance to excel but also dismantle the inequalities that persist in our society.

🌟 Fostering Leaders: The youth of today are the leaders of tomorrow. Supporting their education means nurturing the future leaders, innovators, and change-makers who will shape a more inclusive and equitable world for all.

🌟 Amplifying Voices: Diverse perspectives enrich our understanding of the world. When we support Black and brown youth in education, we amplify their voices and unique contributions, ultimately benefiting society as a whole.

Join me in this important mission at Veritas School of Social Sciences as we work together to make a difference in the lives of our future leaders. Together, we can create a more inclusive and equitable world. 🌍 #TheVeritasWay #EducationMatters #DiversityInEducation #EmpowerYouth

If you'd like to get involved or learn more about our initiatives, feel free to reach out! 📩

Yo! Fitness over 40 is a whole new ballgame. I’m the umpire, the manager and all the players. It’s a team effort to get these gains 💪🏽.

For years, I told myself I was too skinny to lift heavier weights. One day, I decided I was more capable than I thought and stopped listening to that lie.

I’ve never looked back.

My mental focus in 2024 helps me maintain my physical fitness. It’s a commitment to take the best care of my whole self.

How are you incorporating physical fitness in your wellness routine?

#focusfitness #focusfitlife #fitnessfocused #mentalfocus #blackgirlfitness #homegymlife #fitnessover40

PSA: Moms, take your moments to yourself. Light your candle. Take a long shower. Soak in a hot bath. Do what you need to do to show up as best you can.

I’ve found I can only show up as the best version of myself when I give myself the time and rest I need.

Taking short moments to myself helps me maintain my focus.

How do you maintain your focus as a mom?

#momover40 #momtip #momhacks #mentalfocus #mommentalhealth #homegymlife #fitnessover40

You know what I wish I realized sooner in life?

👇🏽

Weight training makes me feel not just strong in my body, but empowered.

👇🏽

I used to tell myself I was too skinny and not strong enough to lift weights.

👇🏽

One day, I decided I’m capable. Period.

👇🏽 

I turned my doubt into determination to get stronger each day.

👇🏽

The goal for me is overall fitness and strength, not perfection.

👇🏽

Let’s get these gains together, y’all.

#bestversionofmyself #fitnessover40 #blackgirlfitness #womenwholift #myfitnessjourney #fitmomlife #homegymlife #flexyourage

FOCUS on right now being enough. FOCUS on taking care of yourself. FOCUS on being the best version of yourself.

#bestversionofmyself #fitnessover40 #blackgirlfitness #womenwholift #myfitnessjourney #fitmomlife #mentalhealthcommunity #flexyourage

POV: You’re a mom with self-diagnosed high-functioning anxiety and you want a way to focus your energy and attention to make the most out of your day and you find my account. 

#fitnessfocused #blackgirlfitness #homegymlife #fitnessover40 #blackgirlworkout #myfitnessjourney #fitmama

My FOCUS in 2024 is to lean in to my JOY.

As my little brother says, “joy maxing” is where it’s at. You have to find moments to savor the joy that’s all around you. 

Be deliberate and intentional about finding your joy.

You deserve it.
